    • Field Detail

      • usersRepository

        private final UsersRepository usersRepository

      • cleanedUpCities

        private final javafx.beans.property.ListProperty<CityDTO> cleanedUpCities
        This list does not contain any duplicates. To be more specific, it contains each city only once with its latest State. i.e., each city that has its com.broudy.gcm.entity.interfaces.IStatable#previousID set to -1. This list gets updated on every BeanRepository.setBeansList(javafx.collections.ObservableList<? super DTO>) call.

    • Constructor Detail

      • CitiesRepository

        @Inject
public CitiesRepository(UsersRepository usersRepository)
        Constructs the basis of any DTORepository. Initializes the BeanRepository.bean's property and the BeanRepository.superBean with the passed dto as well as initializes BeanRepository.beansList. Constructor calls setupInitialBean(C) and startInternalInitialization().

      • requestCitySaving

        public void requestCitySaving()
        This method sends the server a request to create or update currently selected city. Created/Updated city gets a State.LOCKED state. i.e., it is not released to the public before an employee with UserClassification of CONTENT_MANAGER and up approves it.
